The paper proposes a deep learning-based approach for video compression, which involves using optical flow estimation networks and bi-predictive coding. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Multimedia (cs.MM), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), Information Theory (cs.IT), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Multimedia Systems and Applications (cs.MS). Among these, cs.MM and cs.CV are the most likely categories, as they are directly related to video processing and deep learning-based image/video analysis. The other categories are also relevant, as they involve topics such as data compression, information theory, and machine learning, which are all relevant to the proposed approach.
